<subSubSection id="69C9656EFFE9FF8DFCABF856FAF259A1" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="216C36E5FFE9FF8DFCABF856FAF259A1" blockId="6.[817,1475,1917,2037]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE9FF8DFCABF856FB3259E1" authority="Pocock, 1897" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1897" box="[817,1156,1949,1973]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dasyurus">
<emphasis id="13A7EAF7FFE9FF8DFCABF856FC6B59E1" box="[817,989,1949,1973]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Tityus dasyurus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="45424B14FFE9FF8DFC73F855FB3259E1" author="POCOCK" box="[1001,1156,1949,1973]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="510 - 521" refId="ref4472" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1897. Descriptions of some new species of scorpions of the genus Tityus. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, ser. 6, 12: 510 - 521." type="journal article" year="1897">Pocock, 1897</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. This species was described from “ 
<collectingCountry id="59C47675FFE9FF8DFCEFF875FC465981" box="[885,1008,1981,2005]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Porto Rico</collectingCountry>
”, but Teruel et al. (2020: 12) suggested that it seems to be a South or Central American taxon.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="69C9656EFFE8FF8CFFEBFF23FDEC5D57" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="216C36E5FFE8FF8CFFEBFF23FEB55C36" blockId="7.[113,772,235,771]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="13A7EAF7FFE8FF8CFFEBFF23FF6A5F57" bold="true" box="[113,220,235,259]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Remarks</emphasis>
. Of the 16 confirmed species of scorpions described from these Greater Antillean islands, four (
<emphasis id="13A7EAF7FFE8FF8CFD7CFEC3FD7D5F17" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFD7CFEC3FF475F17" authorityName="Teruel, Rivera &amp; Sanchez" authorityYear="2014" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Microtityus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borincanus">M. borincanus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFE99FEE3FE365F16" authorityName="Teruel, Rivera &amp; Sanchez" authorityYear="2014" box="[259,384,299,322]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Microtityus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santosi">M. santosi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFE0BFEE3FD9F5F17" authorityName="Teruel, Rivera &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2015" box="[401,553,299,323]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alejandroi">T. alejandroi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFDA0FEE3FD7D5F17" authorityName="Santiago-Blay" authorityYear="2009" box="[570,715,299,323]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angelesae">T. angelesae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
) are known for a sex and only one or two adult specimens. Seven species, six of them belonging to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFD23FEA3FD4D5FD6" authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[697,763,363,386]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="13A7EAF7FFE8FF8CFD23FEA3FD4D5FD6" box="[697,763,363,386]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Tityus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, are endemic of 
<collectingCountry id="59C47675FFE8FF8CFEBCFE43FE485FF7" box="[294,510,395,419]" name="Puerto Rico Island" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Puerto Rico Island</collectingCountry>
; Vieques has two ones (
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFFE1FE63FF405F96" authorityName="Teruel, Rivera &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2015" box="[123,246,427,450]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Microtityus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vieques">
<emphasis id="13A7EAF7FFE8FF8CFFE1FE63FF405F96" box="[123,246,427,450]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">M. vieques</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFEA8FE63FE755F97" authorityName="Teruel, Rivera &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2015" box="[306,451,427,451]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alejandroi">
<emphasis id="13A7EAF7FFE8FF8CFEA8FE63FE755F97" box="[306,451,427,451]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">T. alejandroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), whereas Mona Island and Culebrita Island has one species each (
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFDB7FE03FD1A5FB7" authorityName="Armas" authorityYear="2005" box="[557,684,459,483]" class="Arachnida" family="Diplocentridae" genus="Cazierius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="garridoi">
<emphasis id="13A7EAF7FFE8FF8CFDB7FE03FD1A5FB7" box="[557,684,459,483]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">C. garridoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFD7CFE03FF765C56" authorityName="Teruel, Rivera &amp; Sanchez" authorityYear="2014" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Microtityus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santosi">
<emphasis id="13A7EAF7FFE8FF8CFD7CFE03FF765C56" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">M. santosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, respectively). At least two species (
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFDC5FE23FD075C57" authorityName="Armas &amp; Marcano Fondeur" authorityYear="1987" box="[607,689,491,515]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bani">
<emphasis id="13A7EAF7FFE8FF8CFDC5FE23FD075C57" box="[607,689,491,515]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">C. bani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFD73FE23FF065C77" baseAuthorityName="Armas &amp; Marcano Fondeur" baseAuthorityYear="1987" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Heteroctenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abudi">
<emphasis id="13A7EAF7FFE8FF8CFD73FE23FF065C77" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">H. abudi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are shared with Hispaniola and one (
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFDF0FDC3FD6B5C76" baseAuthorityName="C. L. Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[618,733,523,546]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="griseus">
<emphasis id="13A7EAF7FFE8FF8CFDF0FDC3FD6B5C76" box="[618,733,523,546]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">C. griseus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is also found in 
<collectingCountry id="59C47675FFE8FF8CFE92FDE3FE1E5C17" box="[264,424,555,579]" name="Virgin Islands" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
. The only introduced species is 
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFFEBFD83FF4D5C37" baseAuthorityName="De Geer" baseAuthorityYear="1778" box="[113,251,587,611]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Isometrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis id="13A7EAF7FFE8FF8CFFEBFD83FF4D5C37" box="[113,251,587,611]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">I. maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="216C36E5FFE8FF8CFF3BFDA3FDEC5D57" blockId="7.[113,772,235,771]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
Two species (
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFED2FDA3FF105CF7" authority="Santiago-Blay, 2009" authorityName="Santiago-Blay" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jorgeorum">
<emphasis id="13A7EAF7FFE8FF8CFED2FDA3FDE35CD6" box="[328,597,619,643]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Centruroides jorgeorum</emphasis>
Santiago-Blay, 2009
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFF6BFD43FDF85CF7" authority="Santiago-Blay, 2009" authorityName="Santiago-Blay" authorityYear="2009" box="[241,590,651,675]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Centruroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sasae">
<emphasis id="13A7EAF7FFE8FF8CFF6BFD43FEE05CF6" box="[241,342,651,674]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">C. sasae</emphasis>
Santiago-Blay, 2009
</taxonomicName>
) remain to be confirmed and are not listed among the 16 confirmed ones; and one more species (
<taxonomicName id="E6D34D66FFE8FF8CFEA7FD03FD375CB7" authority="Pocock, 1897" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1897" box="[317,641,715,739]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Tityus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dasyurus">
<emphasis id="13A7EAF7FFE8FF8CFEA7FD03FE525CB7" box="[317,484,715,739]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Tityus dasyurus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="45424B14FFE8FF8CFE77FD03FD375CB7" author="POCOCK" box="[493,641,715,739]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" pagination="510 - 521" refId="ref4472" refString="POCOCK, R. I. 1897. Descriptions of some new species of scorpions of the genus Tityus. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, ser. 6, 12: 510 - 521." type="journal article" year="1897">Pocock, 1897</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) is possibly not a Puerto Rican taxon (Teruel et al., 2020).
</paragraph>
